  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Draughtsman",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Candidate must possess at least ITE / Diploma in C&amp;S Engineering.</li>\n  <li>Applicants must have a minimum 2 years of working experience in a Singapore Consultancy firm for the Junior position, and a minimum of 5 years of relevant experience for Senior position.</li>\n  <li>Committed and able to work as a team.</li>\n  <li>Candidates shall have relevant experience in Singapore consultant firm, preparing and drafting structural plan using AutoCAD and Revit.</li>\n  <li>Able to start work immediately.</li>\n  <li>Both genders are welcome to apply.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Job Descripton</strong></u></p>\n<ol>\n  <li>Good understanding in drawings and able to conceptualise what details are necessary for a complete set of drawings.</li>\n  <li>Reasonably knowledgeable and experienced in BIM tools including but not limited to Revit, AutoCAD and Navisworks.</li>\n  <li>To produce multi-disciplinary BIM models in a timely manner and with quality.</li>\n  <li>Reasonably capable in doing multi-disciplinary modelling; expected to be at least well-versed in doing structure modelling.</li>\n  <li>To highlight model / drawing discrepancies, missing information or potential issues to Project Manager.</li>\n  <li>Able to propose solutions to the discrepancies.</li>\n  <li>Assist in preparation of BIM documentation such as RFI, sheets, schedules, 3D presentation, report, drawing list, tracking list, chronological order of events and time sheet.</li>\n  <li>Assist in the initial setup of BIM projects, including but not limited to project template, Revit family library, title block, CDE and workflows.</li>\n  <li>Assist in development of BIM standards, protocol and library.</li>\n  <li>To support collaborations with project architects, engineers, clients, consultants and contractors in terms of BIM implementation.</li>\n</ol>",
